    question: "Should I keep all my savings in a high-yield account?",
    answer: "High-yield savings is ideal for <strong>emergency funds and short-term goals</strong> (1-3 years). For longer-term goals (5+ years), you may earn more in diversified investments despite higher risk. A common approach: 3-6 months of expenses in high-yield savings for emergencies, additional savings for 1-3 year goals, then invest the rest for long-term growth."
